---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
import { SITE_NAME } from "../config";
---

<Base
  title="About"
  description="What this archive is, what it is not, where the material comes from, and how to reach us about corrections or takedowns."
>
  <div class="content-col py-8">
    <h1 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight">About</h1>

    <section class="mt-8 border-t border-border pt-6">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold">What this is</h2>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted">
        On 20 July 2026, students marched on Parliament in New Delhi and were
        met with tear gas and lathi charges. Much of what happened that day was
        filmed by the people it happened to, and posted publicly, on platforms
        that do not promise to keep anything.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted">
        {SITE_NAME} keeps a copy. It is a static archive of publicly posted
        video from that day and the months that led to it, preserved so it stays
        findable after the feeds have moved on.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-8 border-t border-border pt-6">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold">Where the material comes from</h2>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted">
        The priority is footage posted by people who were there, rather than
        material from news organisations — this is a record of what
        participants saw and chose to publish.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted">
        Every entry keeps its attribution: the platform, the account that posted
        it, and a link to the original post. That link is on every item in the
        feed. Attribution is never stripped, and the original is always one tap
        away so you can check it against the source yourself.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-8 border-t border-border pt-6">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold">What this is not</h2>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted">
        This is not a news organisation and it is not an investigation. Nothing
        here has been independently verified. What this site can tell you is
        that a given video was publicly posted by a given account on a given
        date, and that a copy has been kept — no more than that.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted">
        Descriptions are written from what is actually visible in the footage.
        Where a clip's framing is contested, or where the archive cannot tell
        what it is looking at, the description says so plainly instead of
        guessing. If you know better than the description does, the form below
        is the fastest way to fix it.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted">
        The cover image on the home page is artwork, not footage from the day.
        Everything in the archive itself is real material from real posts.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted">
        It is also not a social platform. There are no accounts, no comments,
        and no visitor uploads. There is no live feed and no backend serving
        pages — every page is built ahead of time from a reviewed data file.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-8 border-t border-border pt-6">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold">Timeline</h2>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted">
        The{" "}
        <a href="/timeline/" class="text-accent no-underline hover:underline"
          >timeline</a
        >{" "}
        traces how this started — a remark in the Supreme Court in May 2026,
        through the exam scandals that gave it force, to the march on Parliament
        in July. Each entry links to the reporting it is drawn from, so you can
        read the sources rather than take this site's word for it.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-8 border-t border-border pt-6">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold">Corrections &amp; takedowns</h2>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted">
        If you posted something held here and you want it removed, say so and it
        comes down — no justification needed. Corrections and missing context
        are just as welcome.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted">
        Where an entry is wrong rather than unwelcome, it is corrected rather
        than deleted where possible. If media has to be removed, the metadata
        record is kept with a note, so the record of the removal survives.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-4">
        <a
          href="/takedown/"
          class="inline-flex min-h-11 items-center rounded-lg bg-accent px-4 text-sm font-semibold text-bg no-underline"
          >Make a request</a
        >
      </p>
    </section>
  </div>
</Base>
